te","kjv_def":"interpret.","pos":"participle","usage":"interpreted(1x)"},"H8639":{"id":"H8639","lemma":"תַּרְדֵּמָה","translit":"tardêmâh","pron":"tar-day-maw'","derivation":"from H7290 (רָדַם);","strongs_def":"a lethargy or (by implication) trance","kjv_def":"deep sleep.","pos":"feminine noun"},"H8640":{"id":"H8640","lemma":"תִּרְהָקָה","translit":"Tirhâqâh","pron":"teer-haw'-kaw","derivation":"of foreign derivation;","strongs_def":"Tirhakah, a king of Kush","kjv_def":"Tirhakah.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Tirhakah(2x)"},"H8641":{"id":"H8641","lemma":"תְּרוּמָה","translit":"tᵉrûwmâh","pron":"ter-oo-maw'","derivation":"or תְּרֻמָה; (Deuteronomy 12:11), from H7311 (רוּם);","strongs_def":"a present (as offered up), especially in sacrifice or as tribute","kjv_def":"gift, heave offering (shoulder), oblation, offered(-ing).","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"offering(51x), oblation(19x), heave(4x), gifts(1x), offered(1x)"},"H8642":{"id":"H8642","lemma":"תְּרוּמִיָּה","translit":"tᵉrûwmîyâh","pron":"ter-oo-mee-yaw'","derivation":"formed as H8641 (תְּרוּמָה);","strongs_def":"a sacrificial offering","kjv_def":"oblation.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"oblation(1x)"},"H8643":{"id":"H8643","lemma":"תְּרוּעָה","translit":"tᵉrûwʻâh","pron":"ter-oo-aw'","derivation":"from H7321 (רוּעַ);","strongs_def":"clamor, i.e. acclamation of joy or a battle-cry; especially clangorof trumpets, as an alarum","kjv_def":"alarm, blow(-ing) (of, the) (trumpets), joy, jubile, loud noise, rejoicing, shout(-ing), (high, joyful) sound(-ing).","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"shout(11x), shouting(8x), alarm(6x), sound(3x), blowing(2x), joy(2x)"},"H8644":{"id":"H8644","lemma":"תְּרוּפָה","translit":"tᵉrûwphâh","pron":"ter-oo-faw'","derivation":"from H7322 (רוּף) in the sense of its congener H7495 (רָפָא);","strongs_def":"a remedy","kjv_def":"medicine."},"H8645":{"id":"H8645","lemma":"תִּרְזָה","translit":"tirzâh","pron":"teer-zaw'","derivation":"probably from H7329 (רָזָה);","strongs_def":"a species of tree (apparently from its slenderness), perhaps the cypress","kjv_def":"cypress.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"cypress(1x)"},"H8646":{"id":"H8646","lemma":"תֶּרַח","translit":"Terach","pron":"teh'-rakh","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Terach, the father of Abraham; also a place in the Desert","kjv_def":"Tarah, Terah.","pos":"proper locative noun, proper masculine noun","usage":"Terah(11x), Tarah(1x), Tahath(1x)"},"H8647":{"id":"H8647","lemma":"תִּרְחֲנָה","translit":"Tirchănâh","pron":"teer-khan-aw'","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Tirchanah, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Tirhanah."},"H8648":{"id":"H8648","lemma":"תְּרֵין","translit":"tᵉrêyn","pron":"ter-ane'","derivation":"(Aramaic) feminine תַּרְתֵּין; corresponding to H8147 (שְׁנַיִם);","strongs_def":"two","kjv_def":"second, [phrase] twelve, two.","pos":"masculine/feminine noun","usage":"two(1x), second(1x)"},"H8649":{"id":"H8649","lemma":"תׇּרְמָה","translit":"tormâh","pron":"tor-maw'","derivation":"and תַּרְמוּת; or תַּרְמִית; from H7411 (רָמָה);","strongs_def":"fraud","kjv_def":"deceit(-ful), privily.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"deceit(4x), deceitful(1x), privily(1x)"},"H8650":{"id":"H8650","lemma":"תֹּרֶן","translit":"tôren","pron":"to'-ren","derivation":"probably for H766 (אֹרֶן);","strongs_def":"a pole (as a mast or flagstaff)","kjv_def":"beacon, mast.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"mast(2x), beacon(1x)"},"H8651":{"id":"H8651","lemma":"תְּרַע","translit":"tᵉraʻ","pron":"ter-ah'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H8179 (שַׁעַר);","strongs_def":"a door; by implication, a palace","kjv_def":"gate mouth.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"gate(1x), mouth(1x)"},"H8652":{"id":"H8652","lemma":"תָּרָע","translit":"târâʻ","pron":"taw-raw'","derivation":"(Aramaic) from H8651 (תְּרַע);","strongs_def":"a doorkeeper","kjv_def":"porter.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"porters(1x)"},"H8653":{"id":"H8653","lemma":"תַּרְעֵלָה","translit":"tarʻêlâh","pron":"tar-ay